task.summary: Default task
Different scenarios of how finalize() works
finalize() tests
-When and Why of finalize() -Finalize() in action
-finalize() examples
When to use System.gc()
Explicitly calling finalize()
Example to check finalize() of which class gets executed
Learnt difference btw explicit and implicit call to finalize() - Explicit call, invokes finalize() as a normal method - Implicit call, invoked by System.gc() performs clean up
Another example for explicit call to finalize() , to differentiate btw implicit call using System.gc() and explicit call like function invocation using Objects
Learnt how finalize() reacts to exception: - Normally ignores if error occurred, Clean up process inside finalize() is n't completed - Handled with try-catch so that error isn't ignored

Learnt about lifetime of finalized object:
- Object is created. - Object is un-referenced/un-reachable. Now, object is of no use & occupies un-necessary m/y space. - Object is added to finalization queue of GC, which is invoked by JVM. - Clean-Up activities are performed & Object is finalized. - GC destroys object completely and re-claims the space occupied by un-used object
Best Practice for using finalize()
Learning why of Exception
Checked Exception handle, causes compile -time error .
Checked Exception in detail - What, Why etc. with better real-world analogies to understand it - Did dome examples regarding FileNotFoundException and InterruptedException
UnChecked Exception & it's examples
Why errors are unchecked exceptions
Deciding which are Checked & UnChecked Exception
Exception Handling

Exception Handling in detail: - Why is it needed ? - How is it handled ? - How does JVM deals with exception etc. How does exception affects program flow ? And how does handling helps the program flow smooth ?
Exception handling - How exceptions are processed by JVM
Learn how JVM handles an exception using an example
Exception handling with and without using handlerMethod
CheckedVsUnChecked Exceptions
CheckedVsUnChecked Exceptions explained in detail
Basics of Throw and Throws keyword
Throw and Throws keyword theory
Throw Keyword example
Throw Keyword example
-Create a custom exception class and used that custom exception in my method to throw an exception explicitly -Add method signature on the method which throw a custom exception
Custom exception example using throw and throws keyword
Add CustomTestException for learning
Throws test
ArrayIndexOutOfBounds example
ArrayIndexOutOfBounds explained
Detail of how e.getMessage() got it value from - Cleared misunderstanding that what simply thrown is executed, but catch is performed , with clear message
try-Catch test

try-Catch test 2
-The exception causing code is what we enclose in try block and the exception is caught in catch block

try block with multiple catch blocks
-Catch blocks should be specified such that Main Exception class must always be in the lower catch block -Others will be the possible exception classes in top catch blocks

Nested Try Catch Blocks
-Exception causing code is in deep level of try block -It can be caught in deep level itself, else it will propagate outside to see where exactly it is properly caught -Here, It propagates until Main try-catch , where it is handled

Finally block
-To execute code which needs to be run no matter what happens, basically runs everytime , during error and no error -To close resources used, like db connections, file operations etc.

Throw and Throws better example

Throw and Throws in detail
- Why and When do we use each

Learnt how FileNotFoundException and IOException are related
-Exception handling in java is based on inheritance hierarchy -FileNotFoundException occur due to tried to read contents from a file which doesn't exist using FileInputStream class -So, It's an IOException in general
